h2501.definition: the same as {{h2500}}; change; Cheleph, a place in Palestine; Heleph.

h2502.definition: a primitive root; to pull off; hence (intensively) to strip, (reflex.) to depart; by implication, to deliver, equip (for fight); present, strengthen; arm (self), (go, ready) armed (× man, soldier), deliver, draw out, make fat, loose, (ready) prepared, put off, take away, withdraw self.

h2503.definition: or חֵלֶץ; from {{h2502}}; perhaps, strength; Chelets, the name of two Israelites; Helez.

h2504.definition: from {{h2502}} (in the sense of strength); only in the dual; the loins (as the seat of vigor); loins, reins.

h2505.definition: a primitive root; to be smooth (figuratively); by implication (as smooth stones were used for lots) to apportion or separate; deal, distribute, divide, flatter, give, (have, im-) part(-ner), take away a portion, receive, separate self, (be) smooth(-er).

h2506.definition: from {{h2505}}; properly, smoothness (of the tongue); also an allotment; flattery, inheritance, part, × partake, portion.

h2507.definition: the same as {{h2506}}; portion; Chelek, an Israelite; Helek.

h2508.definition: (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{h2505}}; a part; portion.

h2509.definition: from {{h2505}}; smooth (especially of tongue); flattering, smooth.

h2510.definition: the same as {{h2509}}; bare; Chalak, a mountain of Idumaea; Halak.

h2513.definition: feminine of {{h2506}}; properly, smoothness; figuratively, flattery; also an allotment; field, flattering(-ry), ground, parcel, part, piece of land (ground), plat, portion, slippery place, smooth (thing).

h2516.definition: patronymically from {{h2507}}; a Chelkite or descendant of Chelek; Helkites.

h2517.definition: from {{h2505}}; apportioned; Chelkai, an Israelite; Helkai.

h2518.definition: or חִלְקִיָּהוּ; from {{h2506}} and {{h3050}}; portion of Jah; Chilhijah, the name of eight Israelites; Hillkiah.

h2519.definition: by reduplication from {{h2505}}; properly, something very smooth; i.e. a treacherous spot; figuratively, blandishment; flattery, slippery.

h2520.definition: a form of {{h2513}}; smoothness; Chelkath, a place in Palestine; Helkath.

h2521.definition: from {{h2520}} and the plural of {{h6697}}, with the article inserted; smoothness of the rocks; Chelkath Hats-tsurim, a place in Palestine; Helkath-hazzurim.

h2522.definition: a primitive root; to prostrate; by implication, to overthrow, decay; discomfit, waste away, weaken.

h2524.definition: from the same as {{h2346}}; a father-in-law (as in affinity); father in law.

h2526.definition: the same as {{h2525}}; hot (from the tropical habitat); Cham, a son of Noah; also (as a patronymic) his descendants or their country; Ham.

h2527.definition: from {{h2552}}; heat; heat, to be hot (warm).

h2528.definition: (Aramaic) or חֲמָה; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h2534}}; anger; fury.

h2529.definition: or (shortened) חֵמָה; from the same root as {{h2346}}; curdled milk or cheese; butter.

h2530.definition: a primitive root; to delight in; beauty, greatly beloved, covet, delectable thing, (× great) delight, desire, goodly, lust, (be) pleasant (thing), precious (thing).

h2532.definition: feminine of {{h2531}}; delight; desire, goodly, pleasant, precious.

h2533.definition: from {{h2531}}; pleasant; Chemdan, an Idumaean; Hemdan.

h2534.definition: or (Daniel 11:44) חֵמָא; from {{h3179}}; heat; figuratively, anger, poison (from its fever); anger, bottles, hot displeasure, furious(-ly, -ry), heat, indignation, poison, rage, wrath(-ful). See {{h2529}}.

h2535.definition: from {{h2525}}; heat; by implication, the sun; heat, sun.

h2536.definition: from {{h2535}} and {{h410}}; anger of God; Chammuel, an Israelite; Hamuel.

h2537.definition: or חֲמִיטַל; from {{h2524}} and {{h2919}}; father-in-law of dew; Chamutal or Chamital, an Israelitess; Hamutal.

h2538.definition: from {{h2550}}; pitied; Chamul, an Israelite; Hamul.

h2539.definition: patronymically from {{h2538}}; a Chamulite (collectively) or descendants of Chamul; Hamulites.

h2540.definition: from {{h2552}}; warm spring; Chammon, the name of two places in Palestine; Hammon.

h2541.definition: from {{h2556}}; properly, violent; by implication, a robber; oppressed.

h2542.definition: from {{h2559}}; a wrapping, i.e. drawers; joints.

h2543.definition: or (shortened) חֲמֹר; from {{h2560}}; a male ass (from its dun red); (he) ass.

h2544.definition: the same as {{h2543}}; donkey; Chamor, a Canaanite; Hamor.

h2545.definition: or (shortened) חֲמֹת; feminine of {{h2524}}; a mother-in-law; mother in law.

h2546.definition: from an unused root probably meaning, to lie low; a lizard (as creeping); snail.

h2547.definition: feminine of {{h2546}}; low; Chumtah, a place in Palestine; Humtah.

h2548.definition: from {{h2556}}; seasoned, i.e. salt provender; clean.

h2549.definition: or חֲמִשִּׁי; ordinal from {{h2568}}; fifth; also a fifth; fifth (part).

h2550.definition: a primitive root; to commiserate; by implication, to spare; have compassion, (have) pity, spare.

h2552.definition: a primitive root; to be hot (literally or figuratively); enflame self, get (have) heat, be (wax) hot, (be, wax) warm (self, at).

h2554.definition: a primitive root; to be violent; by implication, to maltreat; make bare, shake off, violate, do violence, take away violently, wrong, imagine wrongfully.

h2555.definition: from {{h2554}}; violence; by implication, wrong; by metonymy unjust gain; cruel(-ty), damage, false, injustice, × oppressor, unrighteous, violence (against, done), violent (dealing), wrong.

h2556.definition: a primitive root; to be pungent; i.e. in taste (sour, i.e. literally fermented, or figuratively, harsh), in color (dazzling); cruel (man), dyed, be grieved, leavened.

h2559.definition: a primitive root; properly, to wrap; hence, to depart (i.e. turn about); go about, withdraw self.

h2560.definition: a primitive root; also	as denominative (from {{h2564}}); properly, to boil up; hence, to ferment (with scum); to glow (with redness); to smear with pitch; daub, befoul, be red, trouble.

h2561.definition: from {{h2560}}; wine (as fermenting); × pure, red wine.

h2563.definition: from {{h2560}}; properly, a bubbling up, i.e. of water, a wave; of earth, mire or clay (cement); also a heap; hence, a chomer or dry measure; clay, heap, homer, mire, motion.

h2564.definition: from {{h2560}}; bitumen (as rising to the surface); slime(-pit).

h2566.definition: from {{h2560}}; red; Chamran, an Idumaean; Amran.

h2567.definition: a denominative from {{h2568}}; to tax a fifth; take up the fifth participle

h2568.definition: masculine חֲמִשָּׁה; a primitive numeral; five; fif(-teen), fifth, five (× apiece).

h2569.definition: from {{h2567}}; a fifth tax; fifth participle

h2570.definition: from an unused root probably meaning, to be stout; the abdomen (as obese); fifth (rib).

h2571.definition: passive participle of the same as {{h2570}}; staunch, i.e. able-bodied soldiers; armed (men), harnessed.

h2573.definition: from the same as {{h2346}}; a skin bottle (as tied up); bottle.

h2574.definition: from the same as {{h2346}}; walled; Chamath, a place in Syria; Hamath, Hemath.

h2575.definition: a variation for the first part of {{h2576}}; hot springs; Chammath, a place in Palestine; Hammath.

h2576.definition: from the plural of {{h2535}} and {{h1756}}; hot springs of Dor; Chammath-Dor, a place in Palestine; Hamath-Dor.

h2577.definition: patrial from {{h2574}}; a Chamathite or native of Chamath; Hamathite.

h2578.definition: from {{h2574}} and {{h6678}}; Chamath of Tsobah; probably the same as {{h2574}}; Chamath-Tsobah; Hamath-Zobah.

h2579.definition: from {{h2574}} and {{h7237}}; Chamath of Rabbah; probably the same as {{h2574}}.; Chamath-Rabbah

h2580.definition: from {{h2603}}; graciousness, i.e. subjective (kindness, favor) or objective (beauty); favour, grace(-ious), pleasant, precious, (well-) favoured.

h2581.definition: the same as {{h2580}}; grace; Chen, a figurative name for an Israelite; Hen.

h2582.definition: probably from {{h2580}} and {{h1908}}; favor of Hadad; Chenadad, an Israelite; Henadad.

h2583.definition: a primitive root (compare {{h2603}}); properly, to incline; by implication, to decline (of the slanting rays of evening); specifically, to pitch a tent; generally to encamp (for abode or siege); abide (in tents), camp, dwell, encamp, grow to an end, lie, pitch (tent), rest in tent.

h2584.definition: from {{h2603}}; favored; Channah, an Israelitess; Hannah.

h2585.definition: from {{h2596}}; initiated; Chanok, an antediluvian patriach; Enoch.

h2586.definition: from {{h2603}}; favored; Chanun, the name of an Ammonite and of two Israelites; Hanun.

h2588.definition: from {{h2583}}; properly, a vault or cell (with an arch); by implication, a prison; cabin.

h2589.definition: from {{h2603}} (in the sense of prayer); supplication; be gracious, intreated.

h2590.definition: a primitive root; to spice; by implication, to embalm; also to ripen; embalm, put forth.

h2592.definition: from {{h2603}} and {{h410}}; favor of God; Channiel, the name of two Israelites; Hanniel.

h2595.definition: from {{h2583}}; a lance (for thrusting, like pitching a tent); javelin, spear.

h2596.definition: a primitive root; (compare {{h2614}}); properly, to narrow; figuratively, to initiate or discipline; dedicate, train up.

h2599.definition: patronymically from {{h2585}}; a Chanokite (collectively) or descendants of Chanok; Hanochites.

h2600.definition: from {{h2580}}; gratis, i.e. devoid of cost, reason or advantage; without a cause (cost, wages), causeless, to cost nothing, free(-ly), innocent, for nothing (nought, in vain.
